						<summary>

						<p>TAḌĀVŪR, ATTUR TALUK, SALEM DISTRICT.</p>						

						<p>Ēkāmranāthasvāmin temple, north wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">••• ••••• Year 7.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is written indifferently.</p>						

						<p>It records a royal order addressed to Vilāḍarāyar and <hi rend="italic">puravariyār</hi> for execution, granting all the land in the village Mēl-gaṅgappāḍi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Puttūr in Āṟṟūr-kkūṟṟam with inclusion of all <hi rend="italic">āyam</hi> (levies) for the worship and maintenance of the premises of the temple of Tiruvēkaṁbam-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār of Taḍāvūr. It was attested by Tāyiluṉalla-perumāḷ and Viḻuppādarāyaṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
